# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Project — what NOT to track
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Raw field data — too large for Git (~58 MB and growing per campaign).
# Distributed via Zenodo as part of the thesis dataset deposit.
data/raw/

# Figures — regenerable from scripts. Heavy (~140 MB).
results/figures/

# Installer backups (created by install_v*.ps1)
backups/

# Ad-hoc artefacts that should not enter the repo
*.zip
repo_inventory.txt
repo_inventory_code.txt

# Internal collaboration notes (process — NOT science)
working_style.md

# Throwaway scripts kept locally (if any)
throwaways/
scratch/

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Project — what TO keep (whitelist overrides for clarity)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Mapping tables and config-like CSVs at the metadata level
!data/metadata/

# Processed / derived data — small, scientifically meaningful, results
# of decisions encoded in config/ that future readers want to inspect.
!data/processed/
!data/slopes/
!data/breakpoints/

# Run ledger and method-choice manifests
!results/runs.csv
!results/chosen_method.csv

# Non-figure result tables (per-technique CSVs, convergence outputs)
!results/sec_robustness/
!results/convergence/
!results/sensitivity_savgol_window/

# Sensitivity sweep — exploratory, has PNGs and stage dirs
results/savgol_window_sensitivity/